## 16. SVM for Regression (SVR)

SVR fits a **tube of width $2\varepsilon$** around predictions — points inside the tube have zero loss.

$$\min_{\mathbf{w}}\; \frac{1}{2}\|\mathbf{w}\|^2 + C\sum_{i}(\xi_i + \xi_i^*)$$

```
y
▲      ●  ← outside tube, penalised
│   ╔══╧════╗  ← ŷ + ε
│   ║  ● ●  ║
│   ║       ║  ← ŷ = wᵀx + b
│   ║  ●    ║
│   ╚════════╝  ← ŷ - ε
│ ●  ← outside tube, penalised
└──────────────────────────► x
```

| Hyperparameter | Effect |
|---|---|
| $C$ | Penalty for points outside tube |
| $\varepsilon$ | Tube width — larger = fewer support vectors |

